Nemba processes more than 400 tons of coffee during harvest. Cherries, collected by over 2,600 individual farmers from 15 neighbouring communes in Kayanza, are brought to Nemba to be cleaned and sorted. .
.
Natural processing isn‚Äôt typical in Burundi, making this particular coffee very exciting, the cherries are brought to raised beds where they are spread out in thin layers and slowly dried over a period of 3 weeks.
.
‚è¨ BREW GUIDE below & on our story ‚è¨
.
.

.

If you closed your eyes you‚Äôd 100% think your drinking it üòç Pineapple is very subtle but there.  It has a light body with this delicate sweetness and it gets sweeter as it cools.  A beautiful coffee and another cracker from @brewboxcoffee_ .

Today‚Äôs coffee has came the whole way from the U S of A üá∫üá∏ from a super duper micro Roastery in LA, now when I say micro I mean a guy roasting coffee in his garage micro üòÖ and that‚Äôs exactly what @robbeanscoffee does, he started his business out of passion for Coffee and he reached out to us to try them, We were sent 3 (Ethiopia, Peru & Guatemala) we‚Äôve decided to review the Washed Guatemalan as we believe it was the better roasted out of the 3 .

It had a lot of sweetness, a good body with very low acidity.  There was taste notes of Caramel and Chocolate with this sweet sticky mouthfeel that lingered right to the finish.  Compared to the Coffees from Peru and Ethiopia, this had a good roast profile and could taste good through Espresso, but we didn‚Äôt try this. .

November‚Äôs @brewboxcoffee_ is here and once again guys I‚Äôm in Love üòç today‚Äôs coffee is a Natural from Ethiopia and it‚Äôs roasted by Scottish Roasters @obadiahcoffeeroasters whom I‚Äôve always wanted to try....Oh! and isn‚Äôt their packaging ‚ô•Ô∏èüëåüèª .

The Nuguse Farm has 10 hectares of coffee spread across 3 different parcels of land in the Huro Hibiro village in Bensa, Sidama. Nuguse grows 74158 and 74160 varieties which are both selections from the Jimma research center. These varieties were selected from wild plants in the Metu-Bishari forest in the Illuababora zone in Western Ethiopia. They are widely distributed varieties across Ethiopia and were selected for their resistance to CO2 and high yield. .
Nuguse‚Äôs coffee is all processed and dried at his family home and he only produces natural coffee.
.
.
‚¨áÔ∏èT H E - C O F F E E‚¨áÔ∏è
Location: Nuguse Mare
Origin: Ethiopia
Varietal: 74158 & 74160
Process: Natural
Roast: Filter.
Altitude: 1800m
Roasted Notes: Strawberry, Vanilla and Magnolia
.
.
Taste Notes ‚Ä¢ Straight up Strawberries üçìü§òüèª I love it when the Roaster get the taste notes üëåüèª üçì on the nose and in the Cup, this coffee packed a flavour ü§õüèª, it was juicy, Bright and very sweet with a vanilla cream aftertaste that gave the cup a Strawberey and Cream taste when it cooled üòç it had low acidity with great body and a Clean and Sweet finish.  Dare I say maybe one of the best coffees yet in my Brew Box Subscription üò≤
